The paper presents a novel algorithm for compressive sensing, which is a subfield of information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The algorithm involves optimization techniques, which fall under numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also discusses the performance of the algorithm under different noise models, which is relevant to signal processing (cs.SI) and computer vision (cs.CV).
